    Class Description
    AlcoholAmount
    The measurement / amount of an alcohol usage. E.g. 4-8 beers
    AlcoholAmountDetector
    Detects and labels instances of class AlcoholAmount in text using the alcohol amount TagEx pattern.

    The TagEx search expression for alcohol amounts.
    AlcoholAmountUnits
    The model for alcohol amount unit detection.
    AlcoholCandidate
    A social history candidate for alcohol usage.

    A word that indicates a sentence is an alcohol social history candidate.

    The frequency that an alcohol usage occurs. E.g. "daily", "weekly"
    AlcoholFrequencyDetector
    Detects and labels class AlcoholFrequency instances in text using the general class UsageFrequency label and resolving alcohol related dependencies.

    A verb indicating dependants are related to alcohol usage.

    AlcoholStatus
    A word that indicates whether alcohol usage is ongoing or has ceased.

    Detects and labels class AlcoholStatus in text using class AlcoholStatusPhrases and pre-labeled class UsageStatus instances. Filters on alcohol related linguistic dependency.
    AlcoholStatusPhrases
    Phrases that indicate the current usage status for alcohol.
    AlcoholTemporal
    The time period alcohol usage occurs or occurred in. Phrases like "for thirty years", "at night"
    AlcoholTemporalDetector
    Detects and labels class AlcoholTemporal instances in text using the general class TemporalPhrase and checks for whether there are overlaps with any amounts, frequencies, and whether it is an alcohol related parsing dependency.
    AlcoholType
    The type of alcohol, e.g. beer, liquor.
    AlcoholTypeDetector
    Detects and labels class AlcoholType using the alcohol type phrases and filters for alcohol related linguistic dependency.
    AlcoholTypes
    The model for alcohol types.
    AlcoholUnit
    The unit of measurement of an alcohol usage measurement, used in class AlcoholAmount detection.
    AlcoholUnitDetector
    Labels class AlcoholUnit by checking if any phrases match the list of amount units using a sequence detector, and verifies using a dependencies sanity check.

    The models for the candidate detectors and general social history tasks.
